Proposed timetable:
# TravelPlan: Cologne to Copenhagen Design & New Nordic Weekend, June 6–8 2026

| Day 1 — 2026-06-06 — Arrival, design district, New Nordic dinner | Day 2 — 2026-06-07 — Design museums, architecture, destination dining | Day 3 — 2026-06-08 — Final design stops and return to Cologne |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **1. Outbound flight: Cologne → Copenhagen via Munich** [transport] 08:30–11:55 @ Cologne Bonn Airport / Munich Airport / Copenhagen Airport (€249.00) — Lufthansa itinerary: CGN 08:30 → MUC 09:35, 45-minute layover, then MUC 10:20 → CPH 11:55. Round-trip fare found at €498 for two; half allocated here for cost tracking. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/travel/flights?hl=en&gl=us&curr=EUR&tfs=CBwQAhoeEgoyMDI2LTA2LTA2agcIARIDQ0dOcgcIARIDQ1BIGh4SCjIwMjYtMDYtMDhqBwgBEgNDUEhyBwgBEgNDR05AAUABSAFwAZgBAQ&tfu=EgIIAQ) | **1. Breakfast at Hotel Ottilia** [meal] 08:30–09:30 @ Hotel Ottilia, Bryggernes Plads 7 (€50.00) — Slow breakfast at the boutique hotel before the architecture-focused day. — Links: [link 1](https://www.brochner-hotels.com/our-locations/hotel-ottilia/contact) | **1. Early breakfast and check-out at Hotel Ottilia** [meal] 06:45–07:30 @ Hotel Ottilia, Bryggernes Plads 7 (€40.00) — Early hotel breakfast/coffee and check-out before the morning return flight. Keep it light because of the airport and Vienna layover meals later. — Links: [link 1](https://www.brochner-hotels.com/our-locations/hotel-ottilia/contact) |
| **2. Airport transfer to Hotel Ottilia** [transport] 12:20–12:55 @ Copenhagen Airport to Hotel Ottilia, Bryggernes Plads 7 (€8.00) — Use regional train from CPH to København H, then S-train to Carlsberg Station and a short walk to Hotel Ottilia. Estimated 25–30 minutes by source-backed transit lookup; allow extra time for baggage. — Links: [link 1](https://www.cph.dk/en), [link 2](https://www.rome2rio.com/s/Copenhagen-Airport-CPH/Hotel-Ottilia) | **2. Transfer to Danish Architecture Center** [transport] 09:30–10:00 @ Hotel Ottilia to Danish Architecture Center (€6.50) — From Hotel Ottilia/Carlsberg area to DAC at BLOX. Source-backed route: S-train to København H, then short bus or 15-minute walk to the harborfront; allow around 25–30 minutes. — Links: [link 1](https://dac.dk/en) | **2. Transfer to Copenhagen Airport** [transport] 07:30–08:10 @ Hotel Ottilia to Copenhagen Airport Terminal 3 (€8.00) — Train/S-train route from Carlsberg Station via København H to Copenhagen Airport Terminal 3. Source-backed estimate is about 25–30 minutes; this slot includes buffer. — Links: [link 1](https://www.cph.dk/en), [link 2](https://www.rome2rio.com/s/Copenhagen-Airport-CPH/Hotel-Ottilia) |
| **3. Luggage drop and boutique hotel check-in: Hotel Ottilia** [lodging] 12:55–13:20 @ Hotel Ottilia, Bryggernes Plads 7, 1799 Copenhagen (€484.00) — Stylish boutique hotel in the Carlsberg City District with strong design credentials and sustainability features. Official check-in begins 15:00, so drop bags first and return later if room is not ready. Two-night rate found at €242/night. — Links: [link 1](https://travelstack.nuitee.link/hotels/lpd49f3?checkin=2026-06-06&checkout=2026-06-08&rooms=1&adults=2&occupancies=W3siYWR1bHRzIjoyLCJjaGlsZHJlbiI6W119XQ%3D%3D&language=de&currency=EUR), [link 2](https://www.brochner-hotels.com/our-locations/hotel-ottilia/contact) | **3. Danish Architecture Center at BLOX** [attraction] 10:00–12:30 @ Danish Architecture Center, Bryghuspladsen 10, 1473 Copenhagen (€31.00) — Architecture-focused morning at DAC in the BLOX building: exhibitions, harbor-facing terraces, and Copenhagen urban design context. Sunday hours verified 10:00–18:00; Sunday English guided tour usually 11:00, included with admission. — Links: [link 1](https://dac.dk/en), [link 2](https://copenhagencard.com/attractions/danish-architecture-center?srsltid=AfmBOor44Vm9yIbc1lNLMFiCTNmUtQ2gliDD-smlvGqtJgaHDgH2RrOM) | **3. Airport coffee/pastry: Lagkagehuset or Copenhagen Coffee Lab** [meal] 08:10–09:00 @ Copenhagen Airport Terminal 2/3 (€30.00) — Pre-flight Danish bakery/coffee stop airside. CPH sources list Lagkagehuset and Copenhagen Coffee Lab from around 05:00, suitable for this departure. — Links: [link 1](https://www.cph.dk/en/shopping-dining/dining) |
| **4. Lunch: Vækst** [meal] 13:45–15:00 @ Vækst, Sankt Peders Stræde 34, 1453 Copenhagen (€120.00) — Greenhouse-inspired New Nordic lunch in the Latin Quarter. Saturday service verified 12:00–23:00; good design appeal and moderate Copenhagen pricing. — Links: [link 1](https://cofoco.dk/vaekst/?utm_source=google&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=gmb-website&utm_content=vaekst), [link 2](https://bookings.dineout.is/denmark-vaekst), [link 3](https://guide.michelin.com/us/en/capital-region/copenhagen/restaurant/vaekst) | **4. Walk to Selma via historic center/Nørreport** [transport] 12:30–13:00 @ Danish Architecture Center to Selma (€0.00) — Walk or take transit from DAC toward Nørreport. This keeps the route compact: DAC → central Copenhagen → Selma, near Torvehallerne. — Links: [link 1](https://dac.dk/en), [link 2](http://selmacopenhagen.dk/) | **4. Return flight leg: Copenhagen → Vienna** [transport] 09:40–11:20 @ Copenhagen Airport to Vienna Airport (€125.00) — Austrian OS 992: Copenhagen 09:40 → Vienna 11:20, first leg of the return itinerary. — Links: [link 1](https://www.google.com/travel/flights?hl=en&gl=us&curr=EUR&tfs=CBwQAhoeEgoyMDI2LTA2LTA2agcIARIDQ0dOcgcIARIDQ1BIGh4SCjIwMjYtMDYtMDhqBwgBEgNDUEhyBwgBEgNDR05AAUABSAFwAZgBAQ&tfu=EgIIAQ) |
